This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with WLAN localization, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of optimization techniques to reduce computational requirements, which is a common problem in networking. 

The paper may also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the modeling of electric field behavior and human shadowing effect, which can be related to information theory. 

The paper may also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the automation of routine tasks, which can be related to machine learning. 

The paper may also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the construction of a system (AROMA) for automatic generation of radio maps. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia) as it discusses the use of 3D ray tracing to model the electric field behavior, which can be related to multimedia.
